---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About — Chookaszian Digital Edition" currentPage="about">

  <h1 style="font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3vw, 2.6rem); line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);">About this edition</h1>

  <article class="article">

    <h2>The volume</h2>
    <p>
      Babken Chookaszian (Բաբկէն Չուգասզեան, 1923 Tabriz — 5 November 1997 Yerevan)
      was an Armenian philologist and orientalist, Deputy Director of the Matenadaran
      from 1965 to 1994. This edition presents Volume I of his collected articles,
      published in Yerevan 2022/2023 as a second expanded edition. The printed volume
      runs 573 pages: 550 pages of scholarly text (55 articles + back matter) plus a
      23-page plates insert of family portraits and Matenadaran miniatures.
    </p>

    <h2>Scope of the digital edition</h2>
    <p>
      This is not a facsimile. It is a full scholarly digital edition: extraction,
      structure recovery, TEI P5 encoding, entity enrichment, IIIF v3 image delivery,
      and citation-grounded retrieval. Everything is regenerated from source on every
      commit; nothing is hand-edited HTML.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Every article is TEI P5, validated against RelaxNG and Schematron</li>
      <li>Every printed page break is marked with <code>&lt;pb n="P"/&gt;</code></li>
      <li>Persons and manuscripts are auto-extracted with explicit provenance</li>
      <li>Plates are IIIF v3 with a manuscript register cross-linked from each Canvas</li>
      <li>The "Ask the corpus" retrieval endpoint refuses to answer without citations</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Rights</h2>
    <p>
      Article text is © Levon and Garegin Chugaszyan and remains in copyright in Armenia
      until 2067-12-31 (life+70 from Chookaszian's death in 1997). This site is a
      pre-launch preview served under an implicit family authorisation; a written heirs'
      licence and, for the plates, per-image Matenadaran clearance must be signed before
      any formal publication.
    </p>
    <p>
      New apparatus (metadata, TEI structure, ODD/Schematron, retrieval index, IIIF
      manifests, code) is licensed CC BY 4.0.
    </p>

    <h2>Colophon</h2>
    <p>
      Digital edition editors: Levon and Garegin Chugaszyan. Engineering pipeline:
      Astro (site), TEI Publisher stylesheets adapted, IIIF Presentation 3.0,
      BGE-M3 embeddings + BM25 retrieval, Anthropic Citations API. Source repository:
      <a href="https://github.com/gareginchu/claude-digital-edition">github.com/gareginchu/claude-digital-edition</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>How to cite</h2>
    <p style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .9rem; background: var(--paper-alt); padding: var(--space-4); border-radius: var(--radius); border: 1px solid var(--rule);">
      Chookaszian, Babken. <em>Collected Works, Volume I</em> [digital edition].
      Ed. Levon and Garegin Chugaszyan. Yerevan, 2022/2023.
      <a href="https://gareginchu.github.io/claude-digital-edition">https://gareginchu.github.io/claude-digital-edition</a>.
      Accessed [DATE].
    </p>
    <p style="font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: .875rem; color: var(--ink-mute);">
      Per-article DOIs and a Zenodo concept DOI will be minted at first public release.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
